Many Killed in Clashes in Turkish Southeast, NTV Says

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-10-19T06:59:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/many-killed-in-clashes-in-turkish-southeast-ntv-says-correct-.html
(Corrects attribution in headline.)  The Kurdistan Workers’ Party, or
PKK, killed “many” soldiers in two attacks in southeastern
 Turkey , NTV news channel reported.  The attacks took place in the Yuksekova and Cukurca
districts of the Hakkari province, NTV said, citing news wires.
More than 20 soldiers may have died, NTV reported. The PKK is
listed as a terrorist organization by Turkey, the U.S. and the
European Union.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Bryant at 
 sbryant5@bloomberg.net  